<item>
            <title>[HIVE-3490] Implement * or a.* for arguments to UDFs</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HIVE-3490</link>
                <project id="12310843" key="HIVE">Hive</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;For a random UDF, we should be able to use * or a.* to refer to &quot;all of the columns in their natural order.&quot; This is not currently implemented.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m reporting this as a bug because it is a manner in which Hive is inconsistent with the SQL spec, and because Hive claims to implement *.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;hive&amp;gt; select all_non_null(a.*) from table a where a.ds=&apos;2012-09-01&apos;;&lt;br/&gt;
FAILED: ParseException line 1:25 mismatched input &apos;*&apos; expecting Identifier near &apos;.&apos; in expression specification&lt;/p&gt;</description>
